400
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(log n)

Binary Exponentiation divides the exponent by 2 at every recursive call.

Space Complexity
O(log n)

Due to the recursion stack.

Key Takeaway

The problem can be reduced to counting choices at even and odd indices. By applying Binary Exponentiation, large powers can be computed efficiently, reducing the complexity from O(n) to O(log n) while handling very large values of n.
